<i>adjective</i>: 같다 [갇따] <i>verb</i>: 좋아하다 [조ː아하다], 애호하다 [애ː호하다], 사랑하다 [사랑하다], 가까이하다 [가까이하다] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adjective</i><br>
<dt>같다 [갇따]</dt><br>
<dd>1. same; identical; equal</dd><br>
<dd>서로 다르지 않다.</dd><br>
<dd>Not different from each other.</dd><br>
<dd>2. similar; like</dd><br>
<dd>서로 비슷하다.</dd><br>
<dd>Similar to each other.</dd><br>
<dd>3. such as; like</dd><br>
<dd>무엇과 비슷한 종류에 속해 있음을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A term used to indicate that one belongs to a similar group with something.</dd><br>
<dd>4. if; in case</dd><br>
<dd>'어떤 상황이나 조건이라면'의 뜻을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A term used to indicate 'under a certain situation or condition'.</dd><br>
<dd>5. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>'기준에 알맞은'의 뜻을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A term used to indciate 'meeting a standard'.</dd><br>
<dd>6. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>'마음이나 생각, 형편에 따르자면'의 뜻으로, 실제로는 그렇지 못함을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A term meaning 'according to one's mind, thought, situation, etc.', used to indicate that the reality is the opposite.</dd><br>
<dd>7. just like</dd><br>
<dd>(욕하는 말로) 앞의 말과 다르지 않음을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>(insulting) A term used to indicate that something is not different from what is being referred to.</dd><br>
<dd>8. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>미루어 생각되는 점이 있다.</dd><br>
<dd>Being a fact that one can guess.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>verb</i><br>
<dt>좋아하다 [조ː아하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. like</dd><br>
<dd>무엇에 대하여 좋은 느낌을 가지다.</dd><br>
<dd>To have good feelings toward something.</dd><br>
<dd>2. like; love</dd><br>
<dd>특정한 음식 등을 특별히 잘 먹거나 마시다.</dd><br>
<dd>To have a special liking for a certain food, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. like</dd><br>
<dd>즐겨서 하고 싶어 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To enjoy doing something.</dd><br>
<dd>4. love</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 사람을 아껴 친밀하게 여기거나 서로 마음에 들다.</dd><br>
<dd>To have an affection for and feel intimate toward someone or to like each other.</dd><br>
<dd>5. be happy</dd><br>
<dd>기쁘거나 즐거운 감정을 나타내다.</dd><br>
<dd>To show feelings of happiness or joy.</dd><br>
<dd>6. be laughable</dd><br>
<dd>남의 말이나 행동을 거짓이거나 어리석다고 여겨서 비웃거나 빈정거릴 때 하는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A word that is used to sneer at or ridicule someone as one considers his/her words or behavior untruthful or foolish.</dd><br>
<dt>애호하다 [애ː호하다]</dt><br>
<dd>love; like; be fond of</dd><br>
<dd>사랑하고 좋아하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To like and love something.</dd><br>
<dt>사랑하다 [사랑하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. love</dd><br>
<dd>상대에게 성적으로 매력을 느껴 열렬히 좋아하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To be sexually attracted to someone and like him/her very much.</dd><br>
<dd>2. love; care</dd><br>
<dd>아끼고 소중히 여겨 정성을 다해 위하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To cherish, value, and care for someone with all one's heart.</dd><br>
<dd>3. care; help</dd><br>
<dd>남을 돕고 이해하려고 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To try to help and understand another person.</dd><br>
<dd>4. like; enjoy</dd><br>
<dd>무엇을 매우 좋아하거나 즐기다.</dd><br>
<dd>To like or enjoy something very much.</dd><br>
<dt>가까이하다 [가까이하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. get along; mix with; associate with</dd><br>
<dd>친하게 지내다.</dd><br>
<dd>To be on intimate terms with someone.</dd><br>
<dd>2. enjoy; like</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 것을 좋아하여 가까이 두고 즐기다.</dd><br>
<dd>To be fond of something, and therefore keep it nearby to enjoy.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>